data.description: Located in Hillshire on Bull Mountain, this light and bright traditional home has a perfect floor plan with 3 generously sized bedrooms, a den, and bonus room. The kitchen is open to the nook and family room providing great-room living in addition to formal living and dining rooms. The kitchen is also features newer appliances including built-in convection oven, Bosch dishwasher, and a 5-burner (or 4-burner + griddle) cooktop. The breakfast nook provides a cozy spot to enjoy meals overlooking the backyard flowers. In the adjacent family room, you'll enjoy the cozy gas fireplace, marble tile hearth, built-ins and newer carpeting.This one-owner custom home has been lovingly maintained with a new 50-year roof and recently serviced crawlspace with a new vapor barrier.  Being custom built quality, 2 x 10 truss and 2x6 outer wall construction were used. The attic features thermal sheeting and a solar attic fan for energy efficiency. In the utility room, you'll find a new sink, retractable ironing board, built-in cabinetry, and a hanging rod.The primary ensuite is a spacious retreat, with territorial views of the west hills, city lights and peek-a-boo views of Mt. Hood.  The primary bathroom has a large walk-in closet, dual vanity, jetted tub, walk-in shower, and separate WC.Backyard is accessible from the family room and boasts 3 water features, abundant plants, and perennials, fig trees, multiple seating areas, and a retractable awning over the back patio.Additional features include a 20' x 8' storage loft in the garage, also accessible from the back patio and a gas hookup for a BBQ.  Home currently has a chair lift.Don't miss the chance to own this beautiful property!
